#MEM id=pre-mortem source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/atlas/skills/marketplace/pre-mortem/SKILL.md savings=5%
M||tx|---
M||name|pre-mortem
M||vers|1.0.0
M||md|claude-sonnet-4-6
M||desc|Guide prospective hindsight al to identify project risks before fl occurs. Teams imagine the project has failed spectacularly, then work backward to identify causes. Increases risk identification by 30% compared to traditional planning.
M||lice|MIT
M||meta|
M||auth|SkillForge
M||acad|"HBR 2007 - Performing a Project Premortem by Gary Klein"
M||tx|---
M|Pre-|tx|When this skill activates, you become a pre-mortem facilitator. Your role is to guide us through prospective hindsight al, helping them identify project risks by imagining fl has already occurred.
M|Trig|Acti|
M|Trig|it|`Run a pre-mortem on...`
M|Trig|it|`What cld cause this project to fail?`
M|Trig|it|`Identify project risks for...`
M|Trig|it|`What cld go wrong w/...`
M|Trig|it|`Pre-mortem al`
M|Quic|tx|\| Phase \| Duration \| Output \|
M|Quic|tx|\|-------\|----------\|--------\|
M|Quic|tx|\| 1. Brief \| 2-3 min \| Project context documented \|
M|Quic|tx|\| 2. fl Announcement \| 30 sec \| Mindset shift established \|
M|Quic|tx|\| 3. Independent al \| 3-5 min \| Individual fl reasons \|
M|Quic|tx|\| 4. Round-Robin Collection \| 5-10 min \| Consolidated fl list \|
M|Quic|tx|\| 5. rv and Mitigate \| 10-15 min \| Risk inventory w/ mitigations \|
M|When|Use |
M|When|it|Starting a new project or feature and want to identify risks upfront
M|When|it|Team is overly optimistic and potential downsides need surfacing
M|When|it|Stakeholders need to understand risk before committing resources
M|When|it|After major scope changes to reassess risk landscape
M|When|Use |
M|When|it|Analyzing sec threats specifically (STRIDE, attack trees)
M|When|it|Need structured vulnerability assessment, not general project risk
M|When|Use |
M|When|it|Challenging a specific decision, not brainstorming broad risks
M|Why |tx|Research by Gary Klein demonstrates that **prospective hindsight** (imagining an event has already occurred) increases the ability to identify reasons for outcomes by 30%.
M|Why |**Ke|**
M|Why |tx|1. **Reduces "damn-the-torpedoes" attitude** - Acknowledging fl is possible
M|Why |tx|2. **Creates psychological safety** - Dissenters can voice concerns as al, not criticism
M|Why |tx|3. **Surfaces hidden knowledge** - People share what they know but fear saying
M|Why |tx|4. **Catches blind spots early** - Before commitment and sunk costs
M|Phas|**In|**
M|Phas|it|Project name and objective
M|Phas|it|Timeline and key milestones
M|Phas|it|Team composition (if team context)
M|Phas|it|sc criteria
M|Phas|**Ac|**
M|Phas|tx|1. Document the project scope clearly
M|Phas|tx|2. Identify key stakeholders
M|Phas|tx|3. Note any constraints or dependencies
M|Phas|tx|4. Confirm understanding w/ us
M|Phas|**Ou|** Project context document
M|Phas|tx|**The ct mindset shift.**
M|Phas|Anno|
M|Phas|tx|> "The project has failed. It is [timeline endpoint]. The project did not just miss its goals, it failed spectacularly. Your task now is to identify all the reasons why it failed."
M|Phas|**Im|** Use past tense. The fl has already happened. This is not speculation abt what "might" happen; it "did" happen.
M|Phas|**Fo|**
M|Phas|it|us writes down 5-10 reasons why the project failed
M|Phas|it|No filtering or evaluation yet
M|Phas|it|Include both obvious and "unlikely" causes
M|Phas|it|Consider tc, human, organizational, and external factors
M|Phas|**Fo|**
M|Phas|it|Each person writes independently
M|Phas|it|No discussion or sharing yet
M|Phas|it|Silent reflection maximizes diversity of thought
M|Phas|**Pr|**
M|Phas|tx|> "Write down every reason you can think of for why this project failed. Include causes you consider unlikely. Do not filter yourself. You have 3-5 minutes."
M|Phas|**Ou|** Raw list of fl reasons
M|Phas|**Fo|**
M|Phas|it|rv each fl reason
M|Phas|it|Group by category (see Categories below)
M|Phas|it|No evaluation yet, just collection
M|Phas|**Fo|**
M|Phas|it|Go around the room, each person shares ONE reason
M|Phas|it|Continue rounds until all reasons exhausted
M|Phas|it|Record w/o discussion or debate
M|Phas|it|No "that won't happen" or "we already thought of that"
M|Phas|**Ca|**
M|Phas|tx|1. **tc** - Technology, architecture, implementation
M|Phas|tx|2. **People** - Skills, availability, communication
M|Phas|tx|3. **Process** - Methodology, workflow, coordination
M|Phas|tx|4. **Organizational** - Politics, priorities, resources
M|Phas|tx|5. **External** - mk, cr, regulations, dependencies
M|Phas|tx|6. **Unknown Unknowns** - Black swan events, assumptions
M|Phas|**Ou|** Categorized fl reasons
M|Phas|**Fo|**
M|Phas|tx|1. **Assess likelihood** (1-5 scale)
M|Phas|- 1|Very unlikely
M|Phas|- 2|Unlikely
M|Phas|- 3|Possible
M|Phas|- 4|Likely
M|Phas|- 5|Very likely
M|Phas|tx|2. **Assess impact** (1-5 scale)
M|Phas|- 1|Minor inconvenience
M|Phas|- 2|Delays
M|Phas|- 3|sig setback
M|Phas|- 4|Major fl
M|Phas|- 5|Project-killing
M|Phas|3. *|Likelihood x Impact
M|Phas|4. *|**
M|Phas|- Pr|How to stop it from happening
M|Phas|- De|How to know early if it is happening
M|Phas|- Re|What to do if it happens
M|Phas|tx|5. **Assign ownership** (if team context)
M|Phas|**Pr|**
M|Phas|- Ri|ct, address immediately
M|Phas|- Ri|hi, plan mitigation
M|Phas|- Ri|md, monitor
M|Phas|- Ri|lo, accept or defer
M|Phas|**Ou|** Complete risk inventory (see template)
M|Outp|Gene|
M|Outp|tx|```markdown
M|Pre-|**Pr|** [Name]
M|Pre-|**Da|** [Date]
M|Pre-|**Pa|** [Names or "Individual al"]
M|Proj|- **|** [What sc looks like]
M|Proj|- **|** [Start to end]
M|Proj|- **|** [ct external factors]
M|Risk|tx|\| Priority \| Count \| Top Risk \|
M|Risk|tx|\|----------\|-------\|----------\|
M|Risk|tx|\| ct \| N \| [Highest scoring risk] \|
M|Risk|tx|\| hi \| N \| [Second highest category risk] \|
M|Risk|tx|\| md \| N \| \|
M|Risk|tx|\| lo \| N \| \|
M|R1: |- **|** [tc/People/Process/Organizational/External]
M|R1: |- **|** [How this causes project fl]
M|R1: |- **|** [1-5] \| **Impact:** [1-5] \| **Score:** [L x I]
M|R1: |- **|** [Why this might happen]
M|R1: |- **|**
M|R1: |- Pr|[How to avoid]
M|R1: |- De|[Early wn signs]
M|R1: |- Re|[Contingency plan]
M|R1: |- **|** [Person responsible]
M|R1: |- **|** [Open/Mitigating/Accepted]
M|R1: |tx|[Repeat for each ct risk]
M|High|tx|[Same structure as ct]
M|Medi|[Abb|Name, Category, Score, One-line mitigation]
M|Low |[Lis|Name and score]
M|Acti|tx|\| Action \| Owner \| Due Date \| Risk Addressed \|
M|Acti|tx|\|--------\|-------\|----------\|----------------\|
M|Acti|tx|\| [Specific action] \| [Name] \| [Date] \| R1, R3 \|
M|Revi|- **|** [Date]
M|Revi|- **|** [Weekly/Bi-weekly/Monthly]
M|Revi|tx|```
M|pre-|tx|Validates risk inventory completeness and calculates aggregate statistics.
M|pre-|tx|```bash
M|pre-|tx|python3 .claude/skills/pre-mortem/scripts/pre-mortem.py \
M|pre-|tx|--inventory-path <path-to-risk-inventory.md> \
M|pre-|tx|--validate
M|pre-|tx|```
M|pre-|**Ex|**
M|pre-|- 0|Valid inventory w/ all required fields
M|pre-|- 1|Invalid arguments
M|pre-|- 10|Validation failed (missing required sections)
M|Anti|tx|\| Avoid \| Why \| Instead \|
M|Anti|tx|\|-------\|-----\|---------\|
M|Anti|tx|\| Skipping Phase 2 \| Mindset shift is ct for effectiveness \| Always announce fl explicitly \|
M|Anti|tx|\| Allowing discussion during Phase 3 \| Reduces diversity of thought \| Enforce silent writing \|
M|Anti|tx|\| Filtering "unlikely" causes \| Miss black swan events \| Include all causes, prioritize later \|
M|Anti|tx|\| Stopping at identification \| Risk w/o mitigation is incomplete \| Always complete Phase 5 \|
M|Anti|tx|\| One-time exercise \| Projects evolve, new risks emerge \| Schedule periodic reviews \|
M|Veri|Afte|
M|Veri|it|[ ] All 5 phases done (Brief, fl Announcement, al, Collection, Mitigation)
M|Veri|it|[ ] Risk inventory generated w/ risk scores (Likelihood x Impact)
M|Veri|it|[ ] All ct/hi risks have mitigation strategies
M|Veri|it|[ ] Each mitigation has Prevention, Detection, and rp
M|Veri|it|[ ] Action items assigned w/ owners and due dates
M|Veri|it|[ ] rv schedule established
M|Faci|**Fo|**
M|Faci|it|Emphasize no blame or criticism
M|Faci|it|Senior members speak last in round-robin
M|Faci|it|Celebrate thorough risk identification
M|Faci|it|Treat skeptics as valuable, not negative
M|Faci|**Fo|**
M|Faci|it|Role-play multiple perspectives (developer, us, manager)
M|Faci|it|Challenge your own assumptions explicitly
M|Faci|it|Consider "what wld my critics say?"
M|Exte|1. *|** Add domain-specific risk categories
M|Exte|2. *|** Pre-built risks for common project tp
M|Exte|3. *|** Link to issue trackers for action item follow-up
M|Exte|4. *|** Add financial impact estimation
